ds 2014|website=International Business Times|date=10 August 2015|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n| Nazriya Nazim\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Screenplay|Best Screenplay (Original)]]\n| Anjali Menon\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Remake==\nThe remake rights of the film, for [[Tamil language|Tamil]], [[Telugu language|Telugu]] and [[Hindi]] languages, was jointly acquired by [[Dil Raju]] and [[Prasad V Potluri#Chairman & Managing Director, PVP Ventures Ltd., September 2006 to till date|PVP Cinemas]].\nThe Tamil version of this film, titled Bangalore Naatkal was released on 5 February 2016. The film is directed by Bhaskar and produced by [[Prasad V Potluri|Prasad V. Potluri]] under the production companies PVP Cinema and Bommarillu Bhaskar Cinema. The film stars [[Arya (actor)|Arya]], [[Bobby Simha]], [[Sri Divya]], [[Rana Daggubati]], [[Raai Laxmi]], Parvathy and [[Samantha Ruth Prabhu]] in starring roles.<ref name=\"Remake - Tamil, Telugu and Hindi\">{{cite news|title=Bangalore Days to be remade in Tamil, Telugu and Hindi|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news-interviews/Bangalore-Days-to-be-remade-in-Tamil-Telugu-and-Hindi/articleshow/37506419.cms|newspaper=The Times of India|date=30 June 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"Remake\">{{cite web|title=PVP, Dil Raju to Remake 'Bangalore Days' with Arya, Samantha and Bharath in Lead|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/pvp-dil-raju-remake-bangalore-days-arya-samantha-bharath-lead-603561|website=International Business Times|date=2 July 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"Remake\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-watch-new-teaser-of-the-tamil-remake-of-bangalore-days-2163887|title=Watch: New teaser of the Tamil remake of 'Bangalore Days'|date=9 January 2016|work=dna|accessdate=28 February 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|3668162}}\n\n[[Category:2010s romantic comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:2014 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Malayalam-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Malayalam films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Gopi Sundar]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Films set in Bangalore]]\n", "name_user": "Jellysandwich0", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangalore_Days"}
{"title_page": "Fay Toyne", "text_new": "{{Use Australian English|date=February 2014}}\n{{Infobox tennis biography\n|name                        = Fay Toyne\n|image                       = \n|caption                     = \n|full_name                   = Fay Toyne Moore\n|country                     = {{AUS}}\n|residence                   = \n|birth_date                  = {{birth date and age |df=yes|1943|12|18}}\n|birth_place                 = Australia\n|death_date                  = \n|death_place                 = \n|height                      = \n|college                     = \n|turnedpro                   = \n|retired                     = \n|plays                       = \n|careerprizemoney            = \n|tennishofyear                  = \n|tennishofid                    = \n|website                        = \n|singlesrecord                  = \n|singlestitles                  = \n|highestsinglesranking          = \n|currentsinglesranking          = \n|AustralianOpenresult           = 3R (1962)\n|FrenchOpenresult               = 4R ([[1965 French Championships \u2013 Women's Singles|1965]])\n|Wimbledonresult                = 4R ([[1968 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Women's Singles|1968]])\n|USOpenresult                   = \n|Othertournaments               = \n|MastersCupresult               = \n|WTAChampionshipsresult         = \n|Olympicsresult                 = \n|doublesrecord                  = \n|doublestitles                  =  \n|highestdoublesranking          = \n|currentdoublesranking          = \n|AustralianOpenDoublesresult    = QF (1961, 1963, 1964, 1967)\n|FrenchOpenDoublesresult        = F (1966)\n|WimbledonDoublesresult         = QF (1969)\n|USOpenDoublesresult            = \n|OthertournamentsDoubles        = \n|MastersCupDoublesresult        = \n|WTAChampionshipsDoublesresult  = \n|OlympicsDoublesresult          = \n|Mixed                          = \n|mixedrecord                    = \n|mixedtitles                    = \n|AustralianOpenMixedresult      = 2R (1963, 1964, 1967)\n|FrenchOpenMixedresult          = \n|WimbledonMixedresult           = 4R (1967, 1968)\n|USOpenMixedresult              = \n|OthertournamentsMixedDoubles   = \n|OlympicMixedDoublesresult      = \n}}\n\n'''Fay Toyne''' (born 18 December 1943), also known by her married name '''Fay Toyne Moore''', is a retired tennis player from Australia whose career spanned the 1960s.\n\nToyne was a doubles finalist at the [[1966 French Championships (tennis)|1966 French Championships]]. Partnering [[Jill Blackman]] they were defeated in three sets in the final by compatriots [[Margaret Court|Margaret Smith]] and [[Judy Tegart]].\n\nIn the singles event her best result at a [[Grand Slam (tennis)|Grand Slam]] event was twice reaching the fourth round. At the [[1965 French Championships (tennis)|1965 French Championships]], she lost in the fourth round to [[Annette Van Zyl]], and in the fourth round of the [[1968 Wimbledon Championships]], she was defeated in straight sets by first-seeded and eventual champion [[Billie Jean King]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Wimbledon players archive \u2013 Fay Toyne (Moore)|url=http://www.wimbledon.com/en_GB/scores/draws/archive/players/2eb919f5-eab6-4128-a672-049996e14475/index.html|publisher=AELTC}}</ref>\n\nIn 1964, Toyne won the grass court [[South of England Championships]] in Eastbourne, defeating Lorna Cornell Cawthorn in the final in three sets. In 1966, she won a single tournament in Prague, Czechoslovakia.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article106934674 |title=Fay Toyne scores |newspaper=[[The Canberra Times]] |date=8 September 1966 |page=28 |via=[[National Library of Australia]]}}</ref>\n\n==Grand Slam finals==\n\n===Doubles (1 runner-up)===\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\" \n!style=\"width:40px\"|Result\n!style=\"width:35px\"|Year\n!style=\"width:180px\"|Championship \n!style=\"width:50px\"|Surface\n!style=\"width:140px\"|Partner\n!style=\"width:140px\"|Opponents\n!style=\"width:110px\" 